org.spf4j.test.log.annotations

Annotation Type PrintLogs


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=METHOD)
 @Repeatable(value=PrintLogsConfigs.class)
public @interface PrintLogs
    Annotation to specify custom log printout for a particular unit test. The default log level is controlled via:

    System properties:

    • # default root log level when tests executed from IDE. see TestUtils.class for more info. spf4j.testLog.rootPrintLevelIDE = DEBUG
    • # default root log level. spf4j.testLog.rootPrintLevel = INFO

    Property files: spf4j-test-prtcfg.properties or spf4j-test-prtcfg-ide.properties for ide settings:

    [category(package) name]=[LOG_LEVEL](,[greedy])?

    Author:
    Zoltan Farkas
    See Also:
    org.spf4j.test.log.annotations

    • Element Detail

      • category

        public abstract String category
        Returns:
        the log category to print. ("" is the root category).

      • greedy

        public abstract boolean greedy
        Returns:
        true if we don't want downstream log handlers to receive any logs from this category.
        Default:
        false

      • minLevel

        Returns:
        minimum log level to print.
        Default:
        org.spf4j.log.Level.INFO

      • ideMinLevel

        public abstract Level ideMinLevel
        Returns:
        minimum log level to print when running in the IDE.
        Default:
        org.spf4j.log.Level.DEBUG
